And irony occurs when we stop trying to own what isn’t ours and respect the boundaries of others – we often gain more influence over the situation. By honoring the choices of others, recognizing their humanity, and valuing their right to make decisions, (even decisions, we don’t like) we often gain more significant influence over them. This influence can we used not to manipulate or force our way, but to persuade and encourage toward the way we think is right. Yet when we try to strip others of what is rightly theirs, they will often push us away, giving us less influence. Respecting others is a gateway to leadership, allowing us to exhibit better influence. #mondaymindset #stayinyourlane
